## File-by-File Reasoning and Linkages

### 1. Command Line Interface (`clockwork/cli/`)
The entry points exposing system commands.

*   **[main.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/cli/main.py) & [app.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/cli/app.py):** Initiates exactly which subsystem should respond using Typer. It maps args directly to the specific execution engines (e.g. `clockwork scan` invokes [scanner.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/scanner.py)).
*   **`commands/*.py`:** Separate handler modules encapsulating Typer logic for operations like `agent`, `handoff`, `index`, `registry`, etc.
*   **[__init__.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/__init__.py) & [output.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/cli/output.py):** CLI presentation utilities for cohesive logging and formatting terminal text.

### 2. Context Engine (`clockwork/context/`)
The central state machine and timeline ledger.

*   **[engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/engine.py) ([ContextEngine](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/context/engine.py#37-324)):** Loads `.clockwork/context.yaml`. Handles merges after a [scan](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/scanner.py#80-260), saves timeline histories via [record_change()](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/context/engine.py#306-324), and handles diff checking for task logs. Links dynamically downstream with the Validation Pipeline and the Handoff/Packaging tools.
*   **[models.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/models.py):** Defines the strict `ProjectContext` Pydantic models. Determines exactly what shape a state object ought to have.
*   **[initializer.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/context/initializer.py):** Bootstraps `.clockwork/` state on `clockwork init` without failing entirely via defaults.

### 3. Repository Scanner Engine (`clockwork/scanner/`)
Generates deep static reflections of the codebase without executing user code.

*   **[scanner.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/scanner.py) ([RepositoryScanner](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/scanner.py#44-278)):** Orchestrates an `os.walk` to deeply traverse the directory tree. Calls the other modules sequentially to aggregate the `.clockwork/repo_map.json`.
*   **[filters.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/filters.py):** Excludes ignored directories/files (like `.git`, `.env`) referencing `.clockwork/config.yaml`.
*   **[language.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/language.py) & [frameworks.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/frameworks.py):** Detects file dialects by extensions or by checking dependency manifests (`package.json`, `requirements.txt`).
*   **[symbols.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/symbols.py):** A critical AST component that manually parses languages like Python, JavaScript, and Go to extract symbols (classes, functions, import linkages). This is highly essential for graphing.

### 4. Live Context Index Engine (`clockwork/index/`)
Maintains an O(1) file map by monitoring local OS file deltas natively.

*   **[index_engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/index_engine.py) ([LiveContextIndex](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/index_engine.py#43-361)):** Subsystem orchestrator. Directly bridges [watcher.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/watcher.py) (filesystem watchdog) to single file rescans, and ensures the rest of the application ecosystem updates incrementally ([_sync_graph()](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/index_engine.py#281-337), [_sync_context()](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/index_engine.py#338-361)).
*   **[watcher.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/watcher.py):** Starts an asynchronous watchdog process tracking underlying OS I/O events. Debounces to prevent recursion.
*   **[incremental_scanner.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/incremental_scanner.py):** Does the exact same job as [RepositoryScanner](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/scanner.py#44-278) but for solitary files to save processing time on edits.
*   **[storage.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/storage.py):** Wraps the `index.db` SQLite connection, handling file hashes (`compute_file_hash()`) to reject superficial timestamp changes.

### 5. Knowledge Graph Engine (`clockwork/graph/`)
The symbolic property database ensuring safe module interconnections.

*   **[graph_engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/graph/graph_engine.py) ([GraphEngine](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/graph/graph_engine.py#33-128)):** Wires the Storage, Builder, and Queries together. Generates `.clockwork/knowledge_graph.db`. Links primarily with the Brain Manager and Agent Router.
*   **[builder.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/graph/builder.py):** Translates `repo_map.json` and index imports into Nodes and Edges conceptually.
*   **[queries.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/graph/queries.py):** Houses traversals like `who_depends_on()`. During Agent pipeline validation, the AI queries here to ensure its proposed deletion doesn't sever other active codebase dependencies.
*   **[storage.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/index/storage.py):** Direct SQLite CRUD interface.

### 6. Multi-Agent Router & Autonomous Logic (`clockwork/agent/`)
Dispatches tasks, capabilities, and executes the vital protective pipeline.

*   **[router.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/agent/router.py):** The heart of assignment. Parses the queue, binds capability requirements to agents (`AgentRegistry.agents_for_capability()`), and crucially, runs [ValidationPipeline](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/agent/router.py#89-199) holding stages for Rule checks, Brain heuristics, and Context validation. If changes pass, it commits them to the memory log.
*   **[registry.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/agent/registry.py):** Catalogs available local agents and acts as memory broker assigning/unassigning task metrics.

### 7. Brain Manager AI Verification (`clockwork/brain/`)
A tiered deterministic & generative code verification gateway.

*   **[brain_manager.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/brain/brain_manager.py):** Dispatches processing. Reads `.clockwork/config.yaml` to route an LLM request to `.ollama` or `.external` layers. If `MiniBrain` rejects, it forces early exit. Merges the results via greatest severity.
*   **[minibrain.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/brain/minibrain.py):** A fast programmatic python checker asserting line lengths, function depth, and specific deterministic bounds. Avoids slow LLM queries.
*   **[ollama_brain.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/brain/ollama_brain.py) & [external_brain.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/brain/external_brain.py):** Assembles context windows explicitly prompting LLMs to critique codebase designs and risks intelligently based on the AST map.

### 8. Structural Rules Engine (`clockwork/rules/`)
Defines the style and architecture constraints.

*   **[engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/engine.py) ([RuleEngine](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/engine.py#14-88)):** Cycles changed lines into `SafetyEvaluator`, `ArchitectureEvaluator`, and `DevelopmentEvaluator`. If evaluating agents fail, their build fails.
*   **[evaluators.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/evaluators.py) / [loader.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/loader.py):** Translates humans-readable YAML directives via `.clockwork/rules.yaml` into strict regex and pattern conditions. 
*   **[rule_engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/rule_engine.py):** General-purpose reporting struct generator tracking failures.

### 9. System Security Engine (`clockwork/security/`)
Acts as the ultimate block, checking absolute limits.

*   **[security_engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/security/security_engine.py):** Orchestrates the system block. Called frequently by Plugin installations ([verify_plugin()](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/security/security_engine.py#143-146)) and Agent edits ([check_proposed_changes()](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/security/security_engine.py#147-180)).
*   **[file_guard.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/security/file_guard.py):** Tracks access flags. Hardcodes critical directories to block modifications to secrets and configuration components.
*   **[scanner.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/scanner/scanner.py):** Routine active scan of the repo searching for accidentally committed secrets (`.env`, private keys).

### 10. Handoff Engine (`clockwork/handoff/`)
Transfers memory gracefully between users and automated agents.

*   **[engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/engine.py):** Triggers validation, aggregates knowledge sets, renders `next_agent_brief.md`, and serializes a promptable string injection schema JSON. Links highly into Context and Graph dependencies bridging human-readable and machine contexts.
*   **[aggregator.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/handoff/aggregator.py):** Concatenates tasks, timeline notes, recent code errors, and architectural patterns into one object.
*   **[brief_generator.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/handoff/brief_generator.py) / [validator.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/handoff/validator.py):** Markdown templating and `.clockwork` state integrity verification.

### 11. Registry & Packaging Engines
Shares constraints, skills, and plugins across nodes.

*   **Registry (`clockwork/registry/`):** [registry_engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/registry/registry_engine.py) enables users to fetch plugins from `registry.clockwork.dev`. [cache.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/registry/cache.py) works offline.
*   **Packaging (`clockwork/packaging/`):** [packaging_engine.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/packaging/packaging_engine.py) grabs `.clockwork/*`, verifies rule validity dynamically, computes a checksum, and deflates `.zip` archives. [loader.py](file:///d:/var-codes/Clockworker/clockwork_project/clockwork-src/clockwork/rules/loader.py) inverses this operation seamlessly bridging CI/CD pipelines.
